text.tspan: Prevalence of undernourishment vs share of children who are stunted, 2000
Shown on the x-axis is the main FAO hunger indicator. It measures the share of the population that consumes an amount of
calories that is insufficient to cover the energy requirement for an active and healthy life (as defined by the minimum dietary
energy requirement). Shown on the y-axis is the share of children younger than 5 years that are stunted, which means they fall
are two standard deviations from the median height-for-age of the WHO 'Child Growth Standards'.
Share of children who are stunted
Source: UN Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO)
